article.headline: Houston 60, LSU 52
article.story: HOUSTON (AP) -- Lanny Smith scored 19 points and Andre Owens had 18 to lead Houston to a 60-52 win over previously undefeated LSU Tuesday night. Brandon Bass led LSU (8-1) with 16 points and 11 rebounds and Tack Minor scored 11 points. Jaime Llored added 12 points and grabbed 12 rebounds, but had eight of LSU's 15 turnovers. Houston (6-3) led throughout the game and had a 34-24 lead at halftime. Houston shot 41 percent compared to 35 percent shooting for LSU. The win gives the Cougars their first five-game winning streak since the 1997-98 season.
